  <titles>
    <title type="short" as="introduced">Social Security Transitional Benefit Computation Act of 1987</title>
    <title type="official" as="introduced">A bill to amend title II of the Social Security Act to provide for a more gradual 10-year period of transition to the changes in benefit computation rules enacted in the Social Security Amendments of 1977 as they apply to workers attaining age 65 in or after 1982 (and related beneficiaries) and to provide for increases in their benefits accordingly.</title>
